177Lu-DOTATATE. The indirect treatment comparison that our economic analysis was 
based on was of a simple Bucher type, unadjusted for any differences in the 
baseline characteristics across the two trials.
CONCLUSIONS: Given NICE's current stated range of £20,000-30,000 per QALY for 
the cost-effectiveness threshold, based on list prices, only sunitinib might be 
considered good value for money in England and Wales.
FUTURE WORK: Further analysis of individual patient data from RADIANT-3 would 
allow assessment of the robustness of our findings. The data were not made 
available to us by the company sponsoring the trial.
STUDY REGISTRATION: This study is registered as PROSPERO CRD42016041303.
